<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-21-0321 </DOCNO><TEXT>Calistoga, California, with a $450,000 award from the California EnergyCommission (CEC), is starting development on a geothermal district-heatingsystem for 36 structures. The district-heating system will include manydowntown businesses and three city buildings. 210{sup 0}F geothermalwater is expected to be pumped from the production well(s), located nearPacheteau's spa, and pass through a plate heat exchanger nearby. At theheat exchanger, fresh water in a separate, closed loop will be heatedand circulated through the system. The geothermal water will be injectedback into the reservoir through an injection well drilled at the southernend of town.</TEXT></DOC>